ck JavaScript\n                script(src=\"/public/js/jquery.min.js\")\n                //.. other common JS files\n\nelse\n    block content\n    block JavaScript\n```\n\nAnd my **page.jade** looks like :\n\n``` javascript\nextends layout.jade\n\nblock content\n    h1 Hey ! This is weird !\n\nblock append JavaScript\n    script(src=\"/page_specific.js\")\n```\n\nWhen the page is not requested with AJAX, there are no problems, it looks like :\n\n``` javascript\ndoctype html\n    html(lang=\"fr\")\n        head\n            //....\n        body\n            div.main_content\n                block content\n                    h1 Hey ! This is weird\n\n            block JavaScript\n                script(src=\"/public/js/jquery.min.js\")\n                script(src\"page_specific.js\")\n```\n\nBut when it is requested with AJAX, all the common JS files that should only be included if `locals.xhr` is false are also included in the response (I don't want to re-load jQuery, since it's already there) :\n\n``` javascript\nh1 Hey ! This is weird\nscript(src=\"/public/js/jquery.min.js\")\nscript(src\"page_specific.js\")\n```\n\nAm I doing something wrong ? Is it because templates are not dynamic ? Any help much appreciated !\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pugjs/pug/issues/1618/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pugjs/pug/issues/1618/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]